The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

NATION BRIEFS

 Ahmedabad, Sept. 4 (PTI): Investigators looking for Girs Asiatic lion poachers have arrested two persons allegedly belonging to a pan-national poaching syndicate. 

 A Gujarat CID team scoured five states and arrested the duo in Madhya Pradesh. Police found that the poachers had stalked their quarry on foot for days, but are yet to come across bones, nails or pelts of the lions in the Gir sanctuary. 

 Pune (PTI): A court has extended till Friday the police remand of Bangalore-based software professional Laxman Kailas, who allegedly posted an obscene profile of Shivaji on Orkut, a social networking website. The 25-year-old was arrested by Pune police on September 1. 

 New Delhi (PTI): Delhi High Court has restrained a Jodhpur-based company from selling soft drinks under the trademark Facta, which is similar to global beverages giant Coca-Colas trademark Fanta. Accepting Cokes contention that this was an infringement of its trademark, the court also granted damages of Rs 5 lakh to Coca-Cola. The high court said both labels were similar and therefore the word Facta could cause confusion.

 Junagadh (PTI): Forty passengers of a bus had a narrow escape when the vehicle fell from a bridge after the driver suffered a heart attack. The driver has died.

 Chennai (PTI): A Kuala Lumpur-bound passenger has been arrested from the airport for carrying books published by the banned Sri Lankan militant outfit LTTE. Police said immigration authorities alerted them on Monday night about 29-year-old Suresh. 

 Kanpur (PTI): An undertrial on Tuesday attempted self-immolation inside a court complex alleging that he was refused food and water by jailors. Sonu had asked his relatives standing outside for water, which the jailors did not allow.




